{"id": 4795, "title": "Ticket #4795: [EC2] Allow user to specify arbitrary parameters to RunInstances", "description": "<blockquote>\nEC2 feature requests frequently amount to passing new parameter-value pairs to RunInstances().  Adding the ability for a user to directly specify the parameter name and value would allow users to address their specific needs quickly.  It would also reduce the urgency of the corresponding feature request (perhaps even to the point where documentation would be sufficient).</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2014-Dec-22 14:45:21 by tlmiller:</em> <br/>\n\nWe should probably filter some parameters we don't want users changing (and document the list).\n\n<p>Also, what about parameter names with periods in them?</p></blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Jan-28 16:21</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=42451\">[42451]</a></span>: correct doc details of new ec2 parameter specification <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=4795\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4795'); return false;\" title=\"[EC2] Allow user to specify arbitrary parameters to RunInstances\">#4795</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Jan-27 15:59</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=42424\">[42424]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=4795\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4795'); return false;\" title=\"[EC2] Allow user to specify arbitrary parameters to RunInstances\">#4795</a></span>) Document ec2_parameter_names.  (By Todd L Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Dec-29 12:54</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=42048\">[42048]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=4795\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4795'); return false;\" title=\"[EC2] Allow user to specify arbitrary parameters to RunInstances\">#4795</a></span>) Don't allow user-specified parameters to override generated ones. Also, treat dots in parameter names as underscores when looking them up in the job ad.  (By Todd L Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Dec-22 13:56</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=42008\">[42008]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=4795\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4795'); return false;\" title=\"[EC2] Allow user to specify arbitrary parameters to RunInstances\">#4795</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=4796\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4796'); return false;\" title=\"[EC2] Security Group IDs\">#4796</a></span>) Fix build problem. :(  (By Todd L Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Dec-22 11:54</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=42007\">[42007]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=4795\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4795'); r